FBIS4-34322 "drlat118_a_94013" FBIS-LAT-94-118 Daily Report 19 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Embassy Occupants Not To Be Allowed To Leave Island Embassy Occupants Not To Be Allowed To Leave Island PA1906162294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1529 GMT 19 Jun 94 PA1906162294 Mexico City NOTIMEX Spanish BFN [Text] Havana, 19 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- The Cuban Foreign Ministry has announced that the government "categorically" confirmed today that it will deny all persons who have forcefully entered a diplomatic mission permission to leave the island. A Foreign Ministry note published in the weekly JUVENTUD REBELDE reports that the refusal will be maintained "even if they leave the embassy. No exception will be made." The note reported that on 28 May more than 100 people entered the residence of the Belgian ambassador, on 13 June, 20 people broke into the German Embassy compound in a vehicle, and on 15 June, nine people entered the Chilean Consulate.
